stork.feather.util

Class ThreadBell<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.feather.Bell<T>
      • stork.feather.util.ThreadBell<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The resolution type of this ThreadBell.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Future<T>

    public abstract class ThreadBell<T>
extends Bell<T>
    A Bell which starts a Thread to generate its value. This is intended to ease the integration of blocking libraries with Feather, and should not otherwise be used.

      • start

        public ThreadBell<T> start()
        Execute this ThreadBell's run() method on another Thread. This has no effect if the ThreadBell has already been started.
        Returns:
        This ThreadBell.

      • startOn

        public ThreadBell<T> startOn(Bell bell)
        Call start() depending on the resolution of bell. If bell fails, the Throwable it fails with will be used to fail this ThreadBell.
        Parameters:
        bell - the bell whose resolution will start this ThreadBell.
        Returns:
        This ThreadBell.

      • starterBell

        public Bell starterBell()
        Return a Bell that, when rung successfully, will start this ThreadBell. If the returned Bell is failed, the Throwable it fails with will be used to fail this ThreadBell.
